---
title: "Admin Settings — Cuento Docs"
---

      <div class="docs-eyebrow">Admin Panel</div>
      <h1 class="docs-title">Settings</h1>
      <p class="docs-lead">
        The Settings page controls site-wide behaviour — who can do what, how content
        is displayed, and how external services are connected. Changes take effect
        immediately after saving.
      </p>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-settings.png" alt="Admin Settings page screenshot" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Fields</h2>

      <div class="field-list">

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Site name</div>
            <div class="field-values">text</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            The display name of your Cuento instance. Shown in the browser tab, header,
            and anywhere the site refers to itself by name.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Posts per page</div>
            <div class="field-values">number</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            How many posts are shown per page inside a topic thread. Lower values load
            faster; higher values let readers scroll through long threads without
            clicking through pages. Default is <code>20</code>.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">ImgBB API key</div>
            <div class="field-values">text</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            API key for <a href="https://imgbb.com" class="docs-link">ImgBB</a>, the image hosting
            service used when members upload images through the post editor. Without a valid key
            image uploads will fail. Obtain a free key from your ImgBB account dashboard.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Render navlinks after header panel</div>
            <div class="field-values"><span class="val">y</span> / <span class="val">n</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Controls where the navigation links appear relative to the header panel.
            Set to <code>y</code> to render nav links below the header image/banner;
            set to <code>n</code> to render them above it (default).
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Allow adding factions at character creation</div>
            <div class="field-values"><span class="val">y</span> / <span class="val">n</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            When set to <code>y</code>, members can assign their new character to a faction
            during the character creation flow. Set to <code>n</code> to hide that option —
            useful if factions are invite-only or assigned by admins.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Allow users to create factions</div>
            <div class="field-values"><span class="val">y</span> / <span class="val">n</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Lets logged-in members create new factions. Set to <code>n</code> to restrict
            faction creation to admins only.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Allow guests to create factions</div>
            <div class="field-values"><span class="val">y</span> / <span class="val">n</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Lets unregistered visitors create factions. This is independent of the
            user-level setting above — a guest-facing board may have looser rules
            while requiring registration for persistent play.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Allow users to create claims</div>
            <div class="field-values"><span class="val">y</span> / <span class="val">n</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Lets logged-in members submit claims (requests to play specific characters).
            Set to <code>n</code> if claims are managed entirely by staff.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Allow guests to create claims</div>
            <div class="field-values"><span class="val">y</span> / <span class="val">n</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Lets unregistered visitors submit character claims. Useful for open-application
            roleplay boards where registration follows a successful claim.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Allow wanted characters for claims</div>
            <div class="field-values">
              <span class="val">y</span> / <span class="val">n</span> / <span class="val">moderated</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Controls whether members can claim characters from the Wanted Characters list.
            <ul class="docs-list">
              <li><code>y</code> — anyone who meets the claim rules can claim a wanted character directly.</li>
              <li><code>n</code> — wanted characters cannot be claimed through the normal claim flow.</li>
              <li><code>moderated</code> — claims on wanted characters are submitted for staff review before being approved.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Saving</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Click <strong>Save</strong> at the bottom of the page to apply all changes at once.
        All fields are saved together — there is no per-field save. The button briefly
        shows a confirmation state and then returns to idle.
      </p>
